{:component/id :orbiplex/interaction-broker
 :component/title "Interaction Broker"
 :component/type :host-control-plane
 :component/status :partial

 :summary
 "Host-owned coordination primitive for bounded waits, watches, and probes across registered observation sources. It prevents private polling loops and keeps long waits in the bounded deferred-operation control plane."

 :must-implement
 [{:cap/id :interaction-broker-contract-core
   :title "Broker Contract Core"
   :kind :schema-contract
   :based-on ["doc/project/40-proposals/071-sensorium-workbench.md"
              "doc/project/60-solutions/029-bounded-deferred-operations/029-bounded-deferred-operations.md"]
   :schemas ["interaction-broker-watch.v1"
             "interaction-broker-wait.request.v1"
             "interaction-broker-wait.outcome.v1"
             "interaction-broker-probe.v1"
             "deferred-operation-status.v1"]
   :responsibilities
   ["Define observation sources, watch cursors, wait scopes, conditions, caps, deadlines, and timeout behavior"
    "Reject cursor/source mismatch, wait scope mismatch, traversal paths, and malformed deferred operation ids"
    "Reject oversized wait outcome observed and diagnostics payloads before deferred-operation projection"
    "Project completed async waits into deferred-operation-status.v1 result payloads"]
   :status :partial}

  {:cap/id :host-broker-runtime
   :title "Host Broker Runtime"
   :kind :daemon-service
   :based-on ["doc/project/60-solutions/028-temporal-storage-convention/028-temporal-storage-convention.md"
              "doc/project/60-solutions/029-bounded-deferred-operations/029-bounded-deferred-operations.md"]
   :schemas ["interaction-broker-watch.v1"
             "interaction-broker-wait.request.v1"
             "interaction-broker-wait.outcome.v1"
             "interaction-broker-probe.v1"
             "deferred-operation.v1"
             "deferred-operation-status.v1"]
   :responsibilities
   ["Own daemon admission, grant checks, idempotency, deadlines, persistence, and bounded replay windows"
    "Register async waits in the host deferred-operation registry"
    "Expose operator-visible status for active and terminal broker resources"
    "Recover interrupted waits, watches, and probes explicitly on daemon startup"]
   :status :partial
   :status-detail "The daemon now wires an in-process broker runtime, SQLite resource store, host capability dispatch, operator read APIs, BDO registration/polling for broker-owned async waits, JSON-e/module grant-context admission, startup recovery, idempotent recovered replay, and bounded retention. Capability-provider readiness here reflects broker dispatch liveness; concrete source-provider readiness is reported separately by /v1/interaction-broker/providers."}

  {:cap/id :source-provider-registry
   :title "Source Provider Registry"
   :kind :host-extension-point
   :based-on ["doc/project/40-proposals/071-sensorium-workbench.md"]
   :schemas []
   :responsibilities
   ["Let Workbench, Artifact Delivery, Memarium, approvals, and deferred-operation registry provide bounded observation/probe adapters"
    "Keep source facts and concrete probe mechanics owned by their domain component"
    "Prevent broker code from reaching into component-private stores"]
   :status :partial
   :status-detail "The daemon seeds provider rows for the deferred-operation registry and live Workbench terminal/file adapters. Dynamic non-Workbench provider registration/status APIs exist for bounded metadata and readiness reporting with built-in provider mutation protection plus source-kind and capability declaration validation; executable AD, Memarium, approval, and other non-Workbench source adapters remain incomplete."}]

 :may-implement
 [{:cap/id :cross-source-joins
   :title "Cross-Source Joins"
   :kind :future-coordination
   :based-on ["doc/project/40-proposals/071-sensorium-workbench.md"]
   :schemas ["interaction-broker-wait.request.v1"]
   :responsibilities
   ["Evaluate waits over multiple registered sources only after single-source replay windows and source adapters are stable"
    "Keep composed joins host-owned rather than embedding AD, Memarium, approval, or Workbench semantics in Sensorium Core"]
   :status :deferred}]

 :consumes
 ["registered observation sources"
  "host capability grants"
  "deferred-operation registry"
  "Temporal Storage Convention"]

 :produces
 ["interaction-broker-watch.v1"
  "interaction-broker-wait.outcome.v1"
  "interaction-broker-probe.v1"
  "deferred-operation.v1"
  "deferred-operation-status.v1"
  "operator-visible wait/watch/probe status"]

 :notes
 ["Interaction Broker is horizontal host coordination, not a Sensorium Core feature."
  "Timeouts and suspected hangs are diagnostics; process termination remains a connector/operator directive."
  "The current Node implementation includes a daemon runtime slice for wait/watch/probe admission, broker persistence, operator read APIs, deferred-operation-backed waits, live Workbench file/terminal adapters, explicit recovery statuses, startup/operator retention cleanup, dynamic source-provider metadata registration, and validated dynamic provider declarations."]}
